<FIRST>r w PM-DissidentPriest     09-04 0448</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Dissident Priest,430</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ex-Altar Boy Says Dissident Priest Had Sex With Him</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former Catholic altar boy says he had
homosexual relations 12 years ago with the Rev. George A. Stallings
Jr., the black priest who recently defied the Catholic hierarchy in
forming a breakaway congregation, The Washington Post reported today.
   The 28-year-old man, whom the Post did not identify, told the
paper he had oral sex two or three times a week with Stallings in
the church rectory for several months in 1977.
   Stallings could not be reached through telephone calls to his
church Sunday night. Phone messages were left on an answering
machine of his spokesman, but they were not returned.
   The Post quoted the priest, when asked about the allegations by a
reporter, as saying, ``Sir, do your job. I have no comment.''
   But in addressing his congregation Sunday from the pulpit at its
temporary home in a local high school, Stallings said the newspaper
was preparing an article about ``improprieties.''
   ``When you read in the newspaper or see on the television some
story that they ain't got no evidence and they're trying to say they
do, let me tell you something, church, they ain't got no truth,''
Stallings told his congregation without giving further details.
   Cardinal James A. Hickey, who suspended Stallings in July after
the priest formed a separate African-American congregation, and
other leaders of the Washington archdiocese would not comment on the
allegations, the Post said.
   The former altar boy and a former member of the boys choir at St.
Teresa of Avila Catholic Church was quoted by the Post as saying
that Stallings asked him on a summer afternoon in 1977 to kneel on
the carpet with him and break bread together as an act of special
closeness, the newspaper said.
   ``He started touching my ear,'' the Post quoted the man as
saying. ``And one thing led to another and ended upstairs in his
room. And, you know, that was the start of the relationship right
there, at least the sexual relationship.''
   The newspaper did not identify the man, quoting him as saying he
is now a homosexual but is not openly homosexual. But it said he
signed a sworn statement saying the statements he made in an
interview with its reporters ``are true and the events discussed did
occur.''
   The man was quoted by the newspaper as saying he became uneasy
with the relationship and broke it off, never reporting it to church
officials.
   Then 16, he said his only previous sexual experience ``was
kissing girls at school'' but that his relationship with Stallings
``was a deciding factor'' in his sexual orientation now, the
newspaper said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
