<FIRST>r w AM-US-KingFahd     09-04 0140</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-US-King Fahd,120</SECOND>
<HEAD>Washington Visit By Saudi Leader Postponed Second Time</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   King Fahd of Saudi Arabia has postponed a state
visit to the United States for a second time, White House spokesman
Marlin Fitzwater said Monday.
   The Saudi monarch is putting off the scheduled Sept. 14 visit
``due to the pursuit of the peace process (in Lebanon) through the
Arab League,'' Fitzwater told reporters aboard Air Force One as
President Bush returned from vacation in Maine.
   That was the same reason given for the last delay in July. Saudi
officials denied reports then that Fahd was ill.
   Fahd has joined other Arab leaders in efforts to negotiate a
peace among the warring factions in Lebanon. So far, the Arab
League's efforts have been unavailing.
   Fitzwater said the visit will be rescheduled at a ``mutually
convenient date.''
